===其他用途===
A 2004 study conducted by [[Erciyes_University|Erciyes University]] in [[Turkey|Turkey]] found that pomace can also act as a natural [[food_preservative|food preservative]] that interferes with ''[[Escherichia_coli|E. coli]]'', ''[[Salmonella|Salmonella]]'' and ''[[Staphylococcus|Staphylococcus]]'' bacteria. Researchers pulverised the dried pomace from the white [[Turkish_wine|Turkish wine]] grape [[Emir_Karasi|Emir Karasi]] and red [[Kalecik_Karasi|Kalecik Karasi]] grapes; this was mixed with [[ethyl_acetate|ethyl acetate]], [[methanol|methanol]] or water and exposed to 14 different types of food bacteria. All 14 bacteria were inhibited to some degree by the pomace — depending on the grape variety and the concentration of the extract. The red wine Kalecik Karasi grape was the most effective; the researchers believed this was due to the higher concentration of polyphenols in red wine grape skins.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Gaffney |first1=Jacob |date=September 23, 2004 |title=What a Waste! Grape Pomace Kills Food-Spoiling Bacteria |journal=[[Wine_Spectator|Wine Spectator]] |url=http://www.winespectator.com/webfeature/show/id/What-a-Waste-Grape-Pomace-Kills-Food-Spoiling-Bacteria_3402 |access-date=2013-08-14 |archive-date=2016-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303213211/http://www.winespectator.com/webfeature/show/id/What-a-Waste-Grape-Pomace-Kills-Food-Spoiling-Bacteria_3402 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

[[Oenocyanin|Oenocyanin]], a natural red dye and food-coloring agent, is produced from grape pomace. Tartrates ([[potassium_bitartrate|potassium bitartrate]], 'cream of tartar') and [[polyphenols_in_grape|grape polyphenol]]s can also be manufactured from grape pomace.<ref name="Oxford pg 534-535">{{cite book |title=The Oxford Companion to Wine |url=https://archive.org/details/oxfordcompaniont00janc |last= Robinson |first=Jancis (ed.) |edition=Third |year= 2006 |publisher=Oxford University Press |location= Oxford |isbn= 0-19-860990-6 |pages=[https://archive.org/details/oxfordcompaniont00janc/page/534 534]–535}}</ref>。
